# 🌐 Day 14 – Spring Boot Setup & Hello World API

## ✅ What I Did:
- Set up a Spring Boot project using **Spring Initializr**
- Learned about **project structure**:
  - `src/main/java` for business logic
  - `src/main/resources` for configuration (`application.properties`)
- Created my **first REST API** using `@RestController`
- Tested the API locally with Postman/browser

## 🧩 Code Overview:

```java
@RestController
public class HelloController {

    @GetMapping("/hello")
    public String sayHello() {
        return "Hello, World! Welcome to Spring Boot 🚀";
    }
}
